  <steps>
    <step num="0">Preheat oven to 400˚F (200˚C). </step>
    <step num="1">Slice cauliflower into small florets. </step>
    <step num="2">Place cauliflower onto baking sheet and season with salt, pepper, and olive oil. </step>
    <step num="3">Bake in preheated oven for 25 minutes or until lightly browned and a bit crispy. </step>
    <step num="4">In a large bowl, combine all dressing ingredients. Set aside. </step>
    <step num="5">Once cauliflower is cooked, set aside and let cool slightly. </step>
    <step num="6">Dice eggs, onion, and celery. </step>
    <step num="7">In a large bowl, combine cauliflower, eggs, onion, celery, and dressing. </step>
    <step num="8">Garnish with more freshly chopped dill before serving. </step>
    <step num="9">Enjoy! </step>
  </steps>
